00:00:16.449 --> 00:00:18.389
to talk about the Industrial Revolution.

00:00:18.389 --> 00:00:21.900
Although it occurred around the same time
as the French, American, Latin American, and

00:00:21.900 --> 00:00:26.600
Haitian Revolutions - between, say, 1750 and
1850 - the industrial revolution was really

00:00:26.609 --> 00:00:28.359
the most revolutionary of the bunch.

00:00:28.359 --> 00:00:33.119
Past John: No way, dude. All those other revolutions
resulted in, like, new borders and flags and stuff.

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:37.060
Present John: [sigh] We’ve studied 15,000
years of history here at Crash Course, Me

00:00:37.060 --> 00:00:40.560
from the Past. And borders and flags have
changed plenty, and they’re going to keep

00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:44.500
changing. But in all that time, nothing much changed 
about the way we disposed of waste or located

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:50.060
drinking water or acquired clothing. Most people lived
on or very close to the land that provided their food.

00:00:50.070 --> 00:00:55.650
Except for a few exceptions, life expectancy
never rose above 35 or below 25. Education

00:00:55.650 --> 00:00:59.910
was a privilege, not a right. In all those
millennia, we never developed a weapon that

00:00:59.910 --> 00:01:04.579
could kill more than a couple dozen people
at once, or a way to travel faster than horseback.

00:01:04.579 --> 00:01:10.069
For 15,000 years, most humans never owned
or used a single item made outside of their

00:01:10.069 --> 00:01:15.400
communities. Simon Bolivar didn’t change that and
neither did the American Declaration of Independence.

00:01:15.400 --> 00:01:20.579
You have electricity? Industrial Revolution.
Blueberries in February? Industrial Revolution.

00:01:20.579 --> 00:01:26.239
You live somewhere other than a farm? Industrial
Revolution. You drive a car? Industrial Revolution.

00:01:26.240 --> 00:01:32.680
You get twelve years of free, formal education?
Industrial Revolution. Your bed, your antibiotics,

00:01:32.689 --> 00:01:38.729
your toilet, your contraception, your tap
water, your every waking and sleeping second:

00:01:38.729 --> 00:01:40.380
Industrial Revolution.

00:01:40.380 --> 00:01:49.340
